# LUME App Playground - WWDC Audit Report

## 📂 1. File Structure & Component Roles

### 📦 Root & App Delegate
- **[MyApp.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/MyApp.swift) (MemolaneApp)**:
  - **Role**: The main integration point and entry of the SwiftUI application.
  - **Imports**: `SwiftUI`, `CoreText`.
  - **Dependencies**: Uses `LumeIntroView`, `UnveilStoryView`, and `ContentView` depending on `currentScreen` state. Registers the custom `Komorebi` font via Base64 string.
  - **Used By**: OS Launcher.

### 🖼️ Views/Screens
- **[ContentView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Screens/ContentView.swift)**:
  - **Role**: A simple wrapper view transitioning the user to the `HomeScreenView`.
- **[LumeIntroView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Screens/LumeIntroView.swift)**:
  - **Role**: The first view the user sees. It features a deep space zoom background, Apple-style stagger typography animations, and it begins the launch flow.
- **[UnveilStoryView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Screens/UnveilStoryView.swift)**:
  - **Role**: A secondary cinematic intro/onboarding screen with a glassmorphic card explaining the app's purpose. Triggers transition to `main`.
- **[HomeScreenView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Screens/HomeScreenView.swift)**:
  - **Role**: The primary Hub. Uses a `NavigationSplitView` to show a list of memories (sidebar) and the selected memory details (detail).
  - **Dependencies**: `HomeScreenViewModel`, `MemoryCard`, `MemoryView`, `MuseumView`.
- **[MuseumView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Screens/MuseumView.swift)** & **[ARMuseumView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Screens/ARMuseumView.swift)**:
  - **Role**: An ARKit/RealityKit wrapper displaying `.horizontal` plane tracking to view memories as 3D artifacts.
  - **Dependencies**: `LocationManager`, `DescriptionContainerView`, `ImageContainerView`.
  - **Imports**: `RealityKit`, `ARKit`, `CoreLocation`.
- **[OnBoardingView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Screens/OnBoardingView.swift)**:
  - **Role**: A 3D interactive, paginated storytelling view to introduce the user to the app concept using 3D perspective rotations.

### 🧩 Views/Components (The Building Blocks)
- **[MemoryCard.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Components/MemoryCard.swift)**: Minimal list row card displaying a memory title, image, and description.
- **[MemoryView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Components/MemoryView.swift)**: The detailed editing interface for a memory (TextFields, MapKit location picking, PhotoPicker, Camera).
- **[CameraView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Components/CameraView.swift) / [PhotoPickerView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Components/PhotoPickerView.swift)**: `UIViewControllerRepresentable` wrappers for `UIImagePickerController` and `PHPickerViewController`.
- **[DescriptionContainerView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Components/DescriptionContainerView.swift) / [ImageContainerView.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Views/Components/ImageContainerView.swift)**: Pure SwiftUI views rendered into `CGImage` to be used as materials for 3D `ModelEntity` planes in ARKit.

### 🧠 ViewModels & Services
- **[HomeScreenViewModel.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/ViewModels/HomeScreenViewModel.swift)**: Manages `memoryItems` list and `selectedIndex`. Pre-populated with mock data.
- **[OnBoardingViewModel.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/ViewModels/OnBoardingViewModel.swift)**: State machine controlling text body prompts for the onboarding flow.
- **[LocationManager.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Services/LocationManager.swift)** (Assumed existing): Exposes `location` and `heading` via `CLLocationManagerDelegate`.

### 🗄️ Models
- **[MemoryItem.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Models/MemoryItem.swift)**: Defines `id`, `image`, `title`, `body`, and coordinates for Map and AR placement.
- **[OnBoardingModel.swift](file:///m:/SWIFT%20FILES/COPYWWDC26/LUME-1.swiftpm/Models/OnBoardingModel.swift)**: Defines the onboarding structure.

